'''Martin Baturina''' (born 16 February 2003) is a Croatian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] for {{Italian football updater|Como}} club [[Como 1907|Como]] and the [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]].

==Club career==

===Dinamo Zagreb===
Baturina made his debut for [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb II|Dinamo Zagreb II]] on 14 February 2021, when Dinamo's second team lost to [[NK BSK Bijelo Brdo|Bijelo Brdo]] 1–0. He made his debut for [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]]'s first team on 16 May 2021 in the [[2020–21 Croatian First Football League|2020–21 season]], in which they defeated [[HNK Gorica|Gorica]] 3–0.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gnkdinamo.hr/hr/Novosti/Clanak/gavranovicev-hat-trick-debitirao-baturina |title=Gavranovićev hat-trick, debitirao Baturina |publisher=GNK Dinamo Zagreb |language=hr |date=16 May 2021}}</ref> He made his debut in the [[2021–22 Croatian Football Cup|Croatian Football Cup]] on 22 September, when Dinamo defeated [[HNK Orijent|Orient]] 4–1. Eight days later, he made his debut in the [[2021–22 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]] against [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]], which Dinamo won 3–0.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2033188--genk-vs-dinamo-zagreb/events/ |title=Genk 0–3 Dinamo Zagreb |publisher=UEFA |date=30 September 2021}}</ref>

He scored his first goal for Dinamo on 5 March 2022 in a 3–0 victory over [[HNK Šibenik|Šibenik]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vecernji.hr/sport/uzivo-od-15-dinamo-igra-1000-hnl-utakmicu-sibenik-opet-promijenio-trenera-1568428 |title=Bočkaj i Baturina zabili prvijence, Petković 'počistio paučinu' poluvolejem |publisher=Večernji |language=hr |date=5 March 2022 }}</ref> On the final matchday of the [[2021–22 Croatian First Football League|2021–22 season]], he scored a goal and provided an assist in a 3–1 win over [[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/hnl/klubovi/hajduk/video-orsic-i-baturina-zabili-hajduku-u-nadoknadi-za-veliku-festu-u-maksimiru-15200441 |title=VIDEO: Oršić i Baturina zabili Hajduku u nadoknadi za veliku feštu u Maksimiru! |publisher=Sportske novosti |language=hr |date=21 May 2022 }}</ref> On 6 September 2022, he debuted in the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]], in which Dinamo beat [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] 1–0.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2035649/ |title=Dinamo Zagreb 1–0 Chelsea |publisher=UEFA |date=6 September 2022 }}</ref> On 15 July 2023, he scored the only goal in the [[2023 Croatian Football Super Cup|Super Cup]] match against Hajduk Split.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/maksimir-gotovo-rasprodan-sve-je-spremno-za-najveci-derbi-922751 |title=VIDEO Dinamo srušio Hajduk u derbiju i osvojio Superkup! |publisher=24sata |language=hr |date=15 July 2023 }}</ref>

===Como===
On 17 June 2025, Baturina signed a 5-year contract with {{Italian football updater|Como}} club [[Como 1907|Como]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://comofootball.com/en/martin-baturina-joins-como-1907/ |title=MARTIN BATURINA JOINS COMO 1907 |website=comofootball.com |date=17 June 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==

=== Youth ===
Baturina has made appearances for the Croatian youth national teams of [[Croatia national under-15 football team|U15]], [[Croatia national under-16 football team|U16]], [[Croatia national under-18 football team|U18]], [[Croatia national under-19 football team|U19]], and [[Croatia national under-21 football team|U21]].

=== Senior ===
Baturina received his first call-up to [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] by head coach [[Zlatko Dalić]] for the [[Euro 2024 qualifiers|Euro 2024 Qualifiers]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=Croatia |url=https://www.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/teams/56370--croatia/ |access-date=17 December 2023 |website=[[UEFA]] |language=en}}</ref> On 18 November, he made his debut as a substitute in a 2–0 away win against [[Latvia national football team|Latvia]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=Latvia-Croatia |url=https://www.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/match/2036480--latvia-vs-croatia/ |access-date=18 December 2023 |website=[[UEFA]] |language=en}}</ref>

On 20 May 2024. he was selected in the 26-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=20 May 2024 |title=Croatia head coach Dalić presents preliminary EURO 2024 squad |url=https://hns.team/en/news/27852/croatia-head-coach-dalic-presents-preliminary-euro-2024-squad/ |publisher=[[Croatian Football Federation]] |access-date=30 May 2024}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
Baturina has been described as one of Croatia's most exciting youth prospects. Similarly to his compatriot [[Luka Modrić|Luka Modric]], he has been noted for his ability as a [[playmaker]] who can find space and provide key passes for a goal. He has also been praised for his first touch and ability to dribble and operate in tight spaces.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kulig |first=Jacek |date=31 August 2022 |title=Martin Baturina |url=https://footballtalentscout.net/2022/08/31/martin-baturina/ |access-date=21 December 2023 |website=Football Talent Scout |language=en-US}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Baturina is the son of former [[Croatia national football team|Croatian]] international [[Mate Baturina]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Sinovi bivšeg napadača Hajduka napustili Split i potpisali za Dinamo |url=https://www.vecernji.hr/sport/roko-martin-baturina-dinamo-hajduk-split-nogomet-1184901 |access-date=2024-03-10 |website=www.vecernji.hr |language=hr}}</ref> He was born in [[Zurich]] during his father's stint with [[Grasshopper Club Zurich|Grasshoppers]], however he was raised in [[Split, Croatia|Split]], Croatia, before moving to [[Zagreb]] at the age of 14.<ref>{{Cite web |title=On i brat ponikli u Hajduku, a danas je omiljeni dinamovac i najskuplji igrač u Hrvatskoj |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/hrvatska-reprezentacija/martin-baturina-odrastao-je-uz-hajduk-danas-je-mnogima-omiljeni-dinamovac-i-nada-vatrenih---852344.html |access-date=2026-05-28 |website=Gol.hr |language=hr}}</ref> His older brother, [[Roko Baturina|Roko]], is also a professional footballer.

